Outer engine must run this container with --privileged.
This image is FROM docker:24-dind — the inner dockerd cannot create
namespaces / mount overlayfs without outer privileged mode, and the
seeded workload + backdoor containers will fail to start, which in
turn makes verify.sh return false-pass results (checks that rely on
`docker exec $BACKDOOR` silently pass when the backdoor is absent).

The scored surface is the *inner* container's --privileged flag; the
outer one is a dind prerequisite, not part of the evaluation.
